title: For Sale:  Colt SP1 in great condition, plus 3 magazines, sling, bayonet & scabbard
postcontent:
I bought this from its original owner and it looks like it was fired very little. This rifle is super clean. Field stripping it and inspecting the hammer showed that it had almost no finish wear from bolt travel. I've put about 300 rounds through it since acquiring it. Serial is SP137***. I swapped the A1 birdcage muzzle device for a three-prong and replaced the hammer and trigger springs. Both of these mods are of course fully reversible with a few minutes of work and the original parts are included. I repeat: all of the original parts are here! The spring replacement brought the trigger pull down from 8 lbs to about 5.5 lbs with a crisp, clean break. If you get the insatiable urge to put a crazy match trigger in there, it takes standard modern small trigger pins, so your Geisseles and Timneys and such will drop right in. Also included is its sling, an M7 bayonet with M8 sheath, the unmarked black 30rd mag it came to me with, and two gray USGI 20rd mags marked Adventure Line Mfg Co Inc on the floorplates.
